08/10/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Vlado Buckovski, leader of the main opposition Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia (SDSM), must step down along with the SDSM supervisory board as a result of a no-confidence vote at the party's convention Saturday (October 7th), two months after a poor showing in parliamentary elections. 
A special party congress will be held to elect new leaders. 
Former Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska says she plans to run for the top job. 
(Makfax - 08/10/06; A1 TV - 07/10/06)
